00:05:10.943 --> 00:05:14.285
So the kinetic energy starts off at zero,

00:05:14.285 --> 00:05:15.328
it's stationary,

00:05:15.328 --> 00:05:18.968
but then, it starts, the block
starts getting accelerated.

00:05:18.968 --> 00:05:20.095
It starts getting accelerated.

00:05:20.095 --> 00:05:23.708
And the sum, the sum of these two things

00:05:23.708 --> 00:05:27.069
needs to be equal to one-half
times our spring constant

00:05:27.069 --> 00:05:28.811
times D squared.

00:05:28.811 --> 00:05:30.643
And so you can see if you,

00:05:30.643 --> 00:05:32.543
if you were to add these two curves

00:05:32.543 --> 00:05:35.240
